===Etymology===
From {{etyl|frm}} {{term|mental|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|mentalis|mentālis|of the mind, mental|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|mens|mēns|the mind|lang=la}}. Also from {{etyl|la}} {{term|mentum||the chin|lang=la}}, depending on usage.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-mental.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɛntəl}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Of or relating to the [[mind]] or an [[intellect]]ual process.
# {{colloquial|comparable}} [[insane|Insane]], [[mad]], [[crazy]].
#: {{usex|He is the most '''mental''' freshman I've seen yet.}}
#: {{usex|He went '''mental''' on us.}}
# {{colloquial|UK|comparable}} [[enjoyable|Enjoyable]]; [[fun]].
#: {{usex|That was a '''mental''' party last night.}}
# {{anatomy}} Of or relating to the [[chin]] or [[median]] part of the lower [[jaw]], [[genial]].
# {{biology}} Of or relating to the chin-like or lip-like [[structure]].

